<section id="primary" class="content-area">
<main id="main" class="site-main float col-lg-8 col-md-8 col-sm-12 col-xs-12">
<article id="post-159551" class="post-159551 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-featured category-politics tag-disaster-policy tag-floods tag-saulos-chilima tag-utm grow-content-body entry">
<header class="nyasa-header">
<h1 class="nyasa-title">UTM launches appeal for flood victims: Malawi declared state of national disaster</h1> <div class="entry-meta">
<span class="glyphicon glyphicon-calendar"></span> March 9, 2019
<span class="glyphicon glyphicon-user"> </span> James Nthondo -Nyasa Times <a href="https://www.nyasatimes.com/utm-launches-appeal-for-flood-victims-malawi-declared-state-of-national-disaster/#respond"> <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-comment"> </span> Be the first to comment </a>
</div>
</header>
<div class="nyasa-content">
<p>UTM Party has launched an appeal to people for various relief items for victims of flash floods which have cost 23 lives and rendered thousands homeless.<noscript><img  data-lazy-  alt width="479" height="600" data-srcset="https://www.nyasatimes.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG-20190309-WA0002-479x600.jpg 479w, https://www.nyasatimes.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG-20190309-WA0002-239x300.jpg 239w, https://www.nyasatimes.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG-20190309-WA0002.jpg 862w"  data-src="https://www.nyasatimes.com/wp-content/plugins/lazy-load/images/1x1.trans.gif" data-sizes="(max-width: 479px) 100vw, 479px" class="alignright size-large wp-image-159552 lazyload" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEKAAEALAAAAAABAAEAAAICTAEAOw=="><noscript><img src="https://www.nyasatimes.com/wp-content/plugins/lazy-load/images/1x1.trans.gif" data-lazy-src="https://www.nyasatimes.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG-20190309-WA0002-479x600.jpg" class="alignright size-large wp-image-159552" alt width="479" height="600" srcset="https://www.nyasatimes.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG-20190309-WA0002-479x600.jpg 479w, https://www.nyasatimes.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG-20190309-WA0002-239x300.jpg 239w, https://www.nyasatimes.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG-20190309-WA0002.jpg 862w" sizes="(max-width: 479px) 100vw, 479px"></noscript></noscript><img src='data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=%22http://www.w3.org/2000/svg%22%20viewBox=%220%200%20479%20600%22%3E%3C/svg%3E' data-src="https://www.nyasatimes.com/wp-content/plugins/lazy-load/images/1x1.trans.gif" data-lazy-src="https://www.nyasatimes.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG-20190309-WA0002-479x600.jpg" class="lazyload alignright size-large wp-image-159552" alt width="479" height="600" data-srcset="https://www.nyasatimes.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG-20190309-WA0002-479x600.jpg 479w, https://www.nyasatimes.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG-20190309-WA0002-239x300.jpg 239w, https://www.nyasatimes.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG-20190309-WA0002.jpg 862w" data-sizes="(max-width: 479px) 100vw, 479px"><noscript><img   alt="" width="479" height="600" data-srcset="https://www.nyasatimes.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG-20190309-WA0002-479x600.jpg 479w, https://www.nyasatimes.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG-20190309-WA0002-239x300.jpg 239w, https://www.nyasatimes.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG-20190309-WA0002.jpg 862w"  data-src="https://www.nyasatimes.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG-20190309-WA0002-479x600.jpg" data-sizes="(max-width: 479px) 100vw, 479px" class="alignright size-large wp-image-159552 lazyload" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEKAAEALAAAAAABAAEAAAICTAEAOw==" /><noscript><img class="alignright size-large wp-image-159552" src="https://www.nyasatimes.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG-20190309-WA0002-479x600.jpg" alt="" width="479" height="600" srcset="https://www.nyasatimes.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG-20190309-WA0002-479x600.jpg 479w, https://www.nyasatimes.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG-20190309-WA0002-239x300.jpg 239w, https://www.nyasatimes.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG-20190309-WA0002.jpg 862w" sizes="(max-width: 479px) 100vw, 479px" /></noscript></noscript></p>
<figure id="attachment_159538" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-159538" style="width: 600px" class="wp-caption alignright"><noscript><img  data-lazy-  alt width="600" height="400" data-srcset="https://www.nyasatimes.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG-20190308-WA0034-600x400.jpg 600w, https://www.nyasatimes.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG-20190308-WA0034-300x200.jpg 300w, https://www.nyasatimes.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG-20190308-WA0034.jpg 1080w"  data-src="https://www.nyasatimes.com/wp-content/plugins/lazy-load/images/1x1.trans.gif" data-sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" class="size-large wp-image-159538 lazyload" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEKAAEALAAAAAABAAEAAAICTAEAOw=="><noscript><img src="https://www.nyasatimes.com/wp-content/plugins/lazy-load/images/1x1.trans.gif" data-lazy-src="https://www.nyasatimes.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG-20190308-WA0034-600x400.jpg" class="size-large wp-image-159538" alt width="600" height="400" srcset="https://www.nyasatimes.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG-20190308-WA0034-600x400.jpg 600w, https://www.nyasatimes.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG-20190308-WA0034-300x200.jpg 300w, https://www.nyasatimes.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG-20190308-WA0034.jpg 1080w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px"></noscript></noscript><img src='data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=%22http://www.w3.org/2000/svg%22%20viewBox=%220%200%20600%20400%22%3E%3C/svg%3E' data-src="https://www.nyasatimes.com/wp-content/plugins/lazy-load/images/1x1.trans.gif" data-lazy-src="https://www.nyasatimes.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG-20190308-WA0034-600x400.jpg" class="lazyload size-large wp-image-159538" alt width="600" height="400" data-srcset="https://www.nyasatimes.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG-20190308-WA0034-600x400.jpg 600w, https://www.nyasatimes.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG-20190308-WA0034-300x200.jpg 300w, https://www.nyasatimes.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG-20190308-WA0034.jpg 1080w" data-sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px"><noscript><img   alt="" width="600" height="400" data-srcset="https://www.nyasatimes.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG-20190308-WA0034-600x400.jpg 600w, https://www.nyasatimes.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG-20190308-WA0034-300x200.jpg 300w, https://www.nyasatimes.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG-20190308-WA0034.jpg 1080w"  data-src="https://www.nyasatimes.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG-20190308-WA0034-600x400.jpg" data-sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" class="size-large wp-image-159538 lazyload" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEKAAEALAAAAAABAAEAAAICTAEAOw==" /><noscript><img class="size-large wp-image-159538" src="https://www.nyasatimes.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG-20190308-WA0034-600x400.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" srcset="https://www.nyasatimes.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG-20190308-WA0034-600x400.jpg 600w, https://www.nyasatimes.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG-20190308-WA0034-300x200.jpg 300w, https://www.nyasatimes.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG-20190308-WA0034.jpg 1080w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" /></noscript></noscript><figcaption id="caption-attachment-159538" class="wp-caption-text">Chilima sounds appeal  as thousands are left homeless with hundreds injured</figcaption></figure>
<p>In the appeal, UTM president who is also State Vice President Saulos Chilima said it is important that people come to the aid of the victims of the floods.</p>
<p>&#8220;In this hour of need when our fellow citizens have fallen victim to the devastation and destruction of floods, let us rise to the occasion  and come to their rescue,&#8221; said Chilima.</p>
<p>&#8220;We appeal to all Citizens to mobilize relief items for the aid of our sisters and brothers in need. Let us come forward with donations in financial or material resources,&#8221; said Chilima.</p>
<p>The items which UTM is asking people across the political divide should contribute include food items (non perishables), tents, blankets and clothes, plastic sheets, cooking utensils, buckets, plates, cups, basins, mosquito nests, bottled water, soaps and any other items that might be found helpfully appropriate.</p><div class="Zy4QtuqQ" style="clear:both;float:left;width:100%;margin:0 0 20px 0;"><script async src="https://pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js" type="1dd5334ddd0f16a6b9c4b965-text/javascript"></script>
<ins class="adsbygoogle" style="display:block; text-align:center;" data-ad-layout="in-article" data-ad-format="fluid" data-ad-client="ca-pub-6272874513322487" data-ad-slot="1803160709"></ins>
<script type="1dd5334ddd0f16a6b9c4b965-text/javascript">
     (adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).push({});
</script></div>
<p>Government has declared a state of national disaster and President Peter Mutharika has cut short his trip to the northern region to travel to the southern region which has been heavily affected with the floods.</p>
<p>The damage has not spared the energy sector as on Friday the Electricity Generation Company (Egenco) was forced to shut its Nkula and Kapichira Power Stations making Egenco lose 270 megawatts (MW) of hydro generation capacity against the available capacity of 320MW.</p>
<p>The Department of Climate Change and Meteorological Services said the heavy rains were as a result of deep low pressure area which initially developed in the Mozambican Channel and had intensified due to the presence of the Inter-Tropical Convergence Zone oscillating over Southern Malawi.</p>
